================================================================================
                    ENHANCEMENTS AND MODIFICATIONS (2025)
================================================================================

The following substantial enhancements were made by Penthertz to create
Z-Attack-NG:

ARCHITECTURE & MODERNIZATION:
  • Complete Python 3.8+ rewrite with modern coding standards
  • Modular architecture with clear separation of concerns
  • Organized into core, gui, s2, hardware, and data modules
  • Type hints and comprehensive documentation
  • Modern dependency management with requirements.txt

USER INTERFACE:
  • Replaced legacy interface with professional ImGui-based GUI
  • Real-time packet interception display with dual-log system
  • Interactive network topology visualization
  • Context-sensitive menus and tooltips
  • Enhanced visual feedback and status indicators

SECURITY FEATURES:
  • Full Z-Wave S2 (Security 2) decryption support
    - ECDH Curve25519 key exchange capture
    - AES-CCM authenticated encryption/decryption
    - DSK-based device pairing
    - Session management and export
    - SPAN replay protection
  • Enhanced S0 (Security 0) support with improved nonce management
  • Comprehensive security class handling

PROTOCOL SUPPORT:
  • Support for 60+ Z-Wave command classes
  • Z-Wave Plus device detection and parsing
  • Enhanced command class parsers with detailed output
  • Improved frame construction and validation

ANALYSIS & LOGGING:
  • Advanced packet logging with timestamps
  • CSV export functionality for data analysis
  • Nonce capture database with export capabilities
  • S2 session data export for forensics
  • Right-click context menus for easy data copying

HARDWARE SUPPORT:
  • Hardware abstraction layer for device independence
  • Enhanced RfCat integration with better error handling
  • Improved TI RF Kit support
  • Graceful cleanup and resource management

DEVELOPER EXPERIENCE:
  • Modern argparse-based CLI with comprehensive help
  • Debug mode with verbose logging
  • Clean exit mechanisms and signal handling
  • Extensible plugin-ready architecture
  • Comprehensive inline documentation

STABILITY & RELIABILITY:
  • Improved error handling throughout codebase
  • Memory leak fixes
  • Better resource cleanup
  • Crash recovery mechanisms
  • Platform compatibility improvements

All enhancements maintain compatibility with the GPLv3 license and
preserve attribution to the original authors.

