                        RESPONSIBLE USE DISCLAIMER
================================================================================

Z-Attack-NG is a security research and testing tool intended ONLY for:

AUTHORIZED USES:
  ✓ Security research and academic study
  ✓ Authorized penetration testing with written permission
  ✓ Analysis of personally owned Z-Wave networks
  ✓ Security auditing by qualified professionals
  ✓ Educational purposes in controlled environments
  ✓ Vulnerability research and responsible disclosure

PROHIBITED USES:
  ✗ Unauthorized access to Z-Wave networks or devices
  ✗ Malicious attacks, disruption, or denial of service
  ✗ Privacy violations or surveillance without consent
  ✗ Any activity that violates local, state, or federal laws
  ✗ Commercial use without proper authorization
  ✗ Bypassing security measures without authorization

USER RESPONSIBILITIES:
By using this tool, you agree to:
  1. Use the tool legally and ethically at all times
  2. Obtain explicit written authorization before testing any network
  3. Comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and policies
  4. Respect privacy rights and data protection regulations
  5. Use findings responsibly and follow disclosure best practices
  6. Take full personal responsibility for your actions

LEGAL COMPLIANCE:
Users must comply with all applicable laws including but not limited to:
  • Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) in the United States
  • Computer Misuse Act in the United Kingdom
  • EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
  • Local telecommunications and electronic surveillance laws
  • Terms of service for tested networks and devices

